HEADWORD: Boomslange
<hw>Boom"slang*e</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D.
<ets>boom</ets> tree + <ets>slang</ets> snake.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A large South African tree snake (<spn>Bucephalus Capensis</spn>).
Although considered venomous by natives, it has no poison
fangs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Boon</ent>⟦br⟧
